summary: This is an email exchange between Paul Byrne of the NYPD/FBI Task Force and an unidentified recipient regarding efforts to locate and subpoena three individuals connected to the Ghislaine Maxwell case. The email discusses failed attempts to contact one individual and the decision to subpoena all three via FBI offices.

persons.name: Byrne, Paul

persons.context: Author of the email discussing investigative efforts to subpoena three individuals connected to Ghislaine Maxwell.

persons.name: Maxwell, Ghislaine
persons.context: Mentioned as being in recent communications with one of the individuals they are attempting to subpoena.

connections.description: Byrne is part of the task force investigating Maxwell and her associates.

events.title: Email discussion on subpoena strategy
events.description: Law enforcement discusses plans to subpoena three individuals connected to Ghislaine Maxwell after failed contact attempts.

keyFacts: Law enforcement identified three individuals of interest who are not in the New York area.
One individual has made multiple attempts to contact another person in 2020 but only received 'the run around' and no callback.
One of the individuals was recently in communications with Ghislaine Maxwell and was previously deposed.
The plan is to subpoena all three individuals and have FBI offices serve them ASAP.
